A Quick Summary

0. Run ./install-hooks.sh (or: make -f Makefile.reffs install-hooks)
   This installs a pre-push hook that performs the following checks:
     o Make sure every applicable file has licensing
     o Make sure every commit being pushed has Signed-off-by
     o Make sure every push passes style, license, and build checks

1. Configure and build RefFS:
   o cd where-you-want-to-build-reffs
   o mkdir build
   o cd build
   o ../reffs/configure
   o make [-j]
   o make check

Note, to switch to gcc:

make -f Makefile.reffs build -- --with-cc=gcc
